Knot Calculus

If knots are the primitive objects of meaning, then intelligence isn’t operating on words—it operates on ties.

Just as calculus studies rates of change, Knot Calculus studies how meaning changes while identity is preserved.

⸻

Primitive Operations

Tie (⊗)

Create a stable relationship.

A ⊗ B

Examples:

* Fire ⊗ Heat
* Parent ⊗ Child
* Cause ⊗ Effect

⸻

Untie (⊘)

Separate a structure into components.

Analysis.

Reverse engineering.

Debugging.

⸻

Retie (↺)

Reconnect components differently.

Innovation.

Metaphor.

Engineering.

Evolution.

⸻

Tighten (⇑)

Increase constraints.

Greater precision.

Mathematics is often “tightening” language.

⸻

Loosen (⇓)

Reduce constraints.

Exploration.

Brainstorming.

Poetry.

⸻

Mirror (≈)

Determine whether two knots are structurally equivalent despite different appearances.

DNA
≈
Binary Tree
≈
River Delta
≈
Neural Branching

Not identical.

Equivalent under some mapping.

